<h1>🔢 Sequences</h1>
<p><strong>⭐ Warm up:</strong> Can you write a program that prints the numbers from 0 to 9?</p>
<details>
  <summary><code>while</code> loop structure</summary>
  <pre><code class="language-evy">while loop_condition
    loop_body
    // …
end
</code></pre>
  <details>
    <summary>Code hint 🧚</summary>
    <pre><code class="language-evy">x:num
while x &lt;= ❓
    print x
    x = x + ❓
end
</code></pre>
  </details>
</details>
<p>Write programs that generate the first 20 numbers of the following sequences:</p>
<ul>
  <li>⭐️ 0, 2, 4, 6, …</li>
  <li>⭐️ 1, 4, 7, 10, …</li>
  <li>⭐️ 20, 18.5, 17, …</li>
  <li>⭐️ 1, 2, 4, 8, …</li>
  <li>⭐️ 1, 10, 100, 1000, …</li>
  <li>⭐️ 1, 0.5, 0.25, 0.125, …</li>
  <li>⭐️ 1, 3, 6, 10, …</li>
</ul>
<p>
  Use <em>two different</em> variables to track the count used in the loop condition and the printed
  sequence number.
</p>
<details>
  <summary>Code hint 🧚</summary>
  <pre><code class="language-evy">x:num
a:num
while x &lt;= ❓
    print a
    a =  ❓
    x = x + ❓
end
</code></pre>
</details>
<details>
  <summary>Solution: 20th number</summary>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <p>38</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>58</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>-8.5</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>524288</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>10000000000000000000</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>0.0000019073486328125</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>210</p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</details>
<details>
  <summary>Number Sequences 📖</summary>
  <p>
    The first 3 sequences are <strong>arithmetic sequences</strong> where you add the same amount to
    get from one number to the next.
  </p>
  <p>
    The next 3 sequences are <strong>geometric sequences</strong> where you multiply by the same
    amount to get from one number to the next.
  </p>
  <p>
    The last sequence is the <strong>triangle sequence</strong> where each number is the sum of the
    previous number and its position in the sequence.
  </p>
</details>
